chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Environmental protection and economic growth should be treated as a single long-term strategy: communities prosper most when the air, water, and land they rely on stay healthy. Set clear, science-based goals and measure results, but meet them with flexible tools—performance standards, market signals, and time-limited assistance—so businesses can innovate and plan rather than face sudden disruption. Pair environmental rules with targeted transition support for workers and regions, rewarding solutions that cut pollution, reduce waste, and keep local industries competitive.

chatgpt_double_star_rankings.new_statement: Environmental protection and economic growth should be treated as mutually reinforcing, since clean air, water, and healthy land are the foundation of long-term prosperity and public health. It also invests in clean infrastructure and supports small businesses, worker retraining, and community-led transition planning so families and local economies are not left behind.

Invest in local infrastructure, small-business help, and paid retraining/apprenticeships so workers in manufacturing, construction, and service jobs are not left behind.
